{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"XML: Extensible Markup Language","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/XML","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n<ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XML/XML_introduction\">XML introduction</a></li></ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong>Extensible Markup Language</strong> is a strict serialization of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document_Object_Model\">Document Object Model</a>.</p><div class=\"row topicpage-table\" id=\"sect1\">\n    <div class=\"section\" id=\"sect2\"><dl><dl><dt <=\"\" dl=\"\" id=\"sect3\"></dt></dl></dl></div>\n    <div class=\"section\" id=\"sect4\"><dl><dt class=\"landingPageList\" id=\"xml_introduction\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XML/XML_introduction\">XML introduction</a></dt><dd class=\"landingPageList\">XML (Extensible Markup Language) is a markup language similar to HTML, but without predefined tags to use. Instead, you define your own tags designed specifically for your needs. This is a powerful way to store data in a format that can be stored, searched, and shared. Most importantly, since the fundamental format of XML is standardized, if you share or transmit XML across systems or platforms, either locally or over the internet, the recipient can still parse the data due to the standardized XML syntax.</dd></dl></div>\n    </div>"}}],"toc":[],"summary":"The Extensible Markup Language is a strict serialization of the Document Object Model.","popularity":0.0026,"modified":"2022-02-18T09:30:25.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"XML: Extensible Markup Language","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch"},{"title":"XML: Extensible Markup Language","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"XML: Extensible Markup Language","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"XML: Extensible Markup Language","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"XML: Extensible Markup Language","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"XML: Rozszerzalny Język Znaczników","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"},{"title":"XML: Extensible Markup Language","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"XML (可扩展标记语言)","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/xml","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/xml/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/303a6c3b8ec6658d2956c191c50aee0a0e9e4da5","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XML","title":"XML: Extensible Markup Language"}],"pageTitle":"XML: Extensible Markup Language | MDN","noIndexing":false}}